phase2.explanation:
🤖 **Common ViewModel mistakes and fixes.**

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Context in ViewModel | Use AndroidViewModel if needed |
| Non-observable state | Use StateFlow or LiveData |
| Heavy init | Use coroutines |
| Manual creation | Use viewModel() delegate |
| No lifecycle | Use ViewModelScope |

**Fixes:**
```kotlin
// 1. Use AndroidViewModel if needed
class MyViewModel(application: Application) : AndroidViewModel(application)

// 2. Use observable state
private val _count = mutableStateOf(0)

// 3. Use coroutines for heavy work
init {
    viewModelScope.launch {
        // Heavy work
    }
}

// 4. Use viewModel() delegate
val viewModel: MyViewModel = viewModel()

// 5. ViewModelScope for lifecycle-aware coroutines
viewModelScope.launch { /* work */ }
```

